.TH "fc_host_post_event" 9 "fc_host_post_event" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fc_host_post_event \- called to post an even on an fc_host.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" fc_host_post_event
.BI "(struct Scsi_Host *shost "  ","
.BI "u32 event_number "  ","
.BI "enum fc_host_event_code event_code "  ","
.BI "u32 event_data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "shost" 12
host the event occurred on
.IP "event_number" 12
fc event number obtained from \fBget_fc_event_number\fP
.IP "event_code" 12
fc_host event being posted
.IP "event_data" 12
32bits of data for the event being posted
.SH "NOTES"
This routine assumes no locks are held on entry.
